Code  Name                     Meaning
----  -----------------------  ---------------------------------------------------------------
400   Bad Request              The request itself is malformed — bad syntax, invalid JSON,
                               missing required fields. The client sent garbage; the server
                               couldn't even understand it.

401   Unauthorized             You're not authenticated. No valid credentials (missing/invalid
                               token, expired session). Server doesn't know who you are.

403   Forbidden                You ARE authenticated, but you don't have permission.
                               Server knows who you are, but says:
                               "you're not allowed to do this."

404   Not Found                The resource/URL doesn't exist. Wrong endpoint, deleted
                               resource, or typo in the path.

500   Internal Server Error    Something broke on the server side — unhandled exception,
                               bug in code, null pointer, etc. Generic
                               "server crashed while processing" error.

503   Service Unavailable      Server is temporarily unable to handle the request —
                               overloaded, down for maintenance, or a dependency
                               (database, upstream service) is unreachable.
                               Usually temporary.
